The paper deals with the analysis of compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of random matrices is also a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also presents theoretical bounds on the performance of the measurement technique, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
